lign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Sugarfoot Alive:  Reign of Terror at an End!</span><hr size=1> Sugarfoot Alive:  Reign of Terror at an End!<br>
<br>
Senior Agent Mumsley Thunderfoot Reporting<br>
<br>
<br>
The case involving the rash of disappearances and murders in Misty Thicket has finally come to a close.  Deputies in the Thicket began receiving reports of the appearance of a large troll in the vicinity two days ago.  Later that night the troll was spotted with a captive halfling.  The hostage was quickly identified as the long missing (and presumed dead) Sugarfoot Deeppockets.<br>
<br>
Several brave souls immediately congregated to the scene, prepared to risk their lives against the fearsome intruder in order to rescue Sugarfoot Deeppockets.  The troll was quickly discovered to be none other than Snogg; the selfsame troll that had murdered my own father and stolen the prototypes for the fabled gatorskin pie boots.  Snogg was holding Sugarfoot Deeppockets hostage in the hopes that the young halfling might be able to repair the boot prototype, which has been damaged.  Of course my father, Mimsle Thunderfoot, was the only person that knew the secret of the boots but was now deceased, taking the secret to the grave with him.<br>
<br>
Onlookers were too afraid to assault Snogg directly, who was threatening to kill and eat Sugarfoot instantly should anyone attack.  Brave Synica offered to repair the boots in Sugarfoot's stead, at which offer Snogg promised to release Sugarfoot and leave peacefully.  Synica took the broken pieces of the boots and ran back to the Vale while the courageous and noble Fuggin stayed behind to guard over Sugarfoot from an angry and impatient Snogg.  In a remarkable show of ingenuity, Synica formulated a plan to give an ordinary pair of leather boots to Snogg, fooling her into believing that the gatorskin pie boots were repaired.<br>
<br>
In truly despicable act of coward and shame, Snogg decided, despite her word, to kill the halflings present and eat them anyway.  While Fuggin continued to guard over Sugarfoot, Synica and Crakasmaka fought a valiant battle against Snogg and in the end were successful.<br>
<br>
The three heroes were rewarded by the people of the Vale, and Synica for his exceptional cleverness, was offered a position in the Leatherfoot Raiders, which he took with pride.  We are proud to have such a remarkable young halfling join our ranks.<br>
<br>
Sugarfoot Deeppockets has been returned to her father, Mac, who was overjoyed to see here again.  We all wish her the best in a quick recovery from the trauma of this terrible chapter in the history of the Vale.<br>
<br>
The prototypes were returned to myself.  While I search for my father's lost baking journal and research further into the repair of the gatorskin pie boots they will be on loan to the Museum of the Rivervale Historical Society where they will remain on display until it becomes possible to either repair them or create additional pairs of similar boots.<br>
